      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips and add them to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1658234450261-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1658234450261-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1658234450261-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1658234450261-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1658234450261-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice the <strong>chicken breasts portions</strong> into 3 strips per person</p><p>Add 80ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[120ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[160ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> to a large bowl with<strong> half </strong>your<strong> cider vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>–<strong> </strong>this is your <strong>marinade</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> chicken strips</strong> to the <strong>marinade</strong> and give everything a good mix up, then set aside until later</p><p>Tip: This will help to tenderise your chicken!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1658234452795-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1658234452795-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1658234452795-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1658234452795-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1658234452795-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and grate (don't chop) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>grated garlic</strong> to a small pot with your <strong>chilli relish</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>remaining cider vinegar</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Heat the pot over a low heat, stir everything together until fully combined and cook for 2-3 min or until thickened to a syrup-like consistency – this is your <strong>sweet chilli dip</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1658234456945-x200.jpg",
